Exercise 2.9: Simulate an epidemic outbreak¶

In [11]:
import epidemics_helper
import json
import networkx as nx
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def create_graph_from_json(graph, json_file):
    with open(json_file, 'r') as file:
        data = json.load(file)

    for node in data["nodes"]:
        node_id = node["id"]
        coordinates = tuple(node["coordinates"])
        graph.add_node(node_id, coordinates=coordinates)

    for edge in data["links"]:
        source = edge["source"]
        target = edge["target"]
        graph.add_edge(source, target)

    return graph

G = nx.Graph()
json_file = "../data/nyc_augmented_network.json"
G = create_graph_from_json(G, json_file)
print("Graph created successfully.")

Graph created successfully.

sir = epidemics_helper.SimulationSIR(G, beta=10.0, gamma=0.1, verbose=True)
#_printer=epidemics_helper.ProgressPrinter(verbose=True)
print_sir = epidemics_helper.ProgressPrinter(verbose=True)
sir.launch_epidemic(source=23654, max_time=100.0)

susceptible_data = []
infected_data = []
recovered_data = []
time_data = []

n = sir.n_nodes
status_day1 = []
status_day3 = []
status_day30 = []

ts_array = np.linspace(0, 100, 501)
find_i60 = 0
find_r60 = 0

for time_step in ts_array:
    s = 0
    i = 0
    r = 0
    for node in range(0, 26481):
        status = sir.get_node_status(node, time_step)
        if status == 0:
            s+=1
        elif status == 1:
            i+=1
        else:
            r+=1
        if time_step == 1:
            status_day1.append(status)
        if time_step == 3:
            status_day3.append(status)
        if time_step == 30:
            status_day30.append(status)
    if abs(i/n-0.6)<0.01 and find_i60 == 0:
        print("60 percent of the population is infected at ", time_step)
        find_i60=1
    if abs(r/n-0.6)<0.01 and find_r60 == 0:
        print("60 percent of the population is recovered at ", time_step)
        find_r60=1
    susceptible_data.append(s/n)
    infected_data.append(i/n)
    recovered_data.append(r/n)
    time_data.append(time_step)
    

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(time_data, susceptible_data, label='Susceptible', color='blue')
plt.plot(time_data, infected_data, label='Infected', color='red')
plt.plot(time_data, recovered_data, label='Recovered', color='green')

plt.title('SIR Model Simulation')
plt.xlabel('Time')
plt.ylabel('Proportion of Population')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

import random

source_node = random.randint(0, n-1)
source_node_10000 = random.randint(0, n-1)
print(source_node, source_node_10000)
edges = G.edges()
random_edges = random.sample(list(edges), 1000)
random_edges_10000 = random.sample(list(edges), 10000)

G_s1 = G.copy()
G_s1_10000 = G.copy()
G_s1.remove_edges_from(random_edges)
G_s1_10000.remove_edges_from(random_edges_10000)
sir_1000 = epidemics_helper.SimulationSIR(G_s1, beta=10.0, gamma=0.1, verbose=True)
sir_10000 = epidemics_helper.SimulationSIR(G_s1_10000, beta=10.0, gamma=0.1, verbose=True)
status_day30_s1=[]
status_day30_s1_10000 = []
s=0
i=0
r=0
s_10000=0
i_10000=0
r_10000=0
sir_1000.launch_epidemic(source=source_node, max_time=100.0)
for node in range(0, 26481):
    status = sir_1000.get_node_status(node, 30)
    if status == 0:
        s+=1
    elif status == 1:
        i+=1
    else:
        r+=1
    status_day30_s1.append(status)

        adj = list(G.adj[node])
        edges_rm.extend((node, neighb) for neighb in adj)
